<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1943-04-09T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1943-04-09T00:00:00-05:00" n="14" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d14">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">Hopkins Papers: Telegram</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The President’s Special Assistant</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Hopkins</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to Prime Minister <persName type="to">Churchill</persName>
                                </hi><note n="1" xml:id="d14fn1">Channel of transmission not
                                    indicated, but presumably military.</note>
                            </head>
                            <opener>
                                <seg rendition="#left">
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">secret</hi>
                                </seg>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">[<placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>,] <date calendar="gregorian" when="1943-04-09">April 9,
                                    1943</date>.</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>Mr. Harry Hopkins to Prime Minister personal and most secret.</p>
                            <p>Anthony must have misunderstood me relative to my coming to England
                                immediately. The President feels that the time not propitious until
                                situation in Tunisia clarified. He will be in direct touch with you
                                soon.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Harry</hi>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>